==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Underwood
<hw>Un"der*wood`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Small trees and
bushes that grow among large trees; coppice; underbrush; -- formerly
used in the plural.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Shrubs and <qex>underwoods</qex> look well enough while they grow
within the shade of oaks and cedars.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underwork</ent>⟦br⟧
